The paper deals with the discrete logarithm problem in Jacobians of curves over finite fields, which is a topic in cryptography and information theory (cs.CR). The algorithm presented in the paper relies on heuristics similar to those used in the number field sieve or the function field sieve algorithms, which are commonly used in computational number theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the complexity of the algorithm in terms of the size of the finite base fields and the curve genus, which are topics in computational complexity and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper presents a new algorithm for a specific family of curves, which could be of interest to researchers in computational geometry and algebraic geometry (cs.SD, cs.CC).
